title: Cate Blanchett
summary: Catherine Elise Blanchett AC (/ˈblæntʃət/;[2][3] born 14 May 1969) is an Australian actor. Regarded as one of the best actresses of her generation,[4][5] she is noted for her roles in blockbusters, independent films, and stage work. Blanchett is the recipient of numerous accolades, including two Academy Awards, three British Academy Film Awards, three Screen Actors Guild Awards, and three Golden Globe Awards.
